latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Mumma Boys 1st trip to @vishranti_resorts 

The initial plan was to reach there along with kids on Thursday & my husband would accompany us on Friday night, not knowing that he would get stuck in Delhi cause of some emergency. 

The moment he told me that he won’t be able to come, I became so terrified as this was the first time I stepped out of home all alone with my kids and then being in resort alone with two 5 years old kids was even more scary for me considering god forbids if any emergency happens then what am I gonna do. And let me clarify here that having twins is NOT at all same as having 2 kids. So yes I was very scared. 

We went by flight to Dehradun & from airport the resort is an hour away. We requested resort to arrange for the pickup. The resort is an amazing property. They have everything a kid needs for enjoyment and it’s a lush green property with swimming pool, a gym, a pub (where kids aren’t allowed), swings area, a small zoo with many kinds of parrots, swans, roosters, mountain biking and many more things to do. The best part is it’s a pet friendly resort. The food is also tasty but bit spicy for kids so it’s better to inform the chef before every meal that it’s for kids. Also they have the concept of farm to table cause of which it takes approximately 40-45 mins for food to get prepared.

The trip went awesome as the staff in resort was really helpful plus it was so safe there. My kids enjoyed and so did I, even though I wasn’t able to go for spa 😭 

Now I’ve the courage to take them alone for more trips … which they have already said that they want to  go again after 60 days 😂😂

Music: Wander

So much has changed in last one year but the best of all is the way my hair looks now. 

Washdays till April 2021
- oil hair previous night 
- shampoo
- conditioner
- use normal towel for drying hair
- comb hair 
- use cotton pillow cover while sleeping
- use to hate my hair

Washdays since April 2021 
- keep oil on hair for only an hour & use heat cap for 30 mins.

- use cotton tShirt / microfiber towel to remove excess water from hair

It doesn’t bothers me that I spend few hours extra while washing my hair as that has made my hair so healthy & beautiful.

How to make Hair Gel at home

The key ingredient of this gel is Flaxseed also know as अलसी in Hindi.

The easiest way to make this hair gel is:
Take 1 cup of water & add 2 tablespoons of flaxseed. Bring it to a boil & stop cooking once you see a sticky consistency (like the one in video). Add 5 drops of any essential oil like orange lavender to overcome the smell of flaxseed.

However, you can also add methi dana (fenugreek), kalonji (black onion seed), hibiscus flower & leaves, rose petals, rosemary, essential oils like cedar wood, tea tree, pomegranate, grapeseed or whatever suits you…to make the gel more beneficial for hair. But all this is optional.

Have already shared the amazing benefits of flaxseed gel for hair in my previous post.

How to apply:
Method 1: as a hair mask-pour a small amount into your hands and massaging it directly into your hair. Leave on for up to 15 minutes, rinse, and shampoo as normal

Method 2: as hair gel for styling men hair. Just take little gel on palm and apply on wet hair & comb. You will see amazing hold for the entire day. 

Method 3: use it as a pre-conditioning rinse after shampooing 

Method 4: as hair gel for curly/wavy hair. Take 3-4 pumps of gel & rub between the palms and apply on wet hair (after styling products)

Confused about how much & how to use Cantu Curl Activator… worry not cause even I was confused when I started.

I had no idea what pea size meant as everyone’s pea size was different but now I understand WHY it was different. 

Cantu is very thick in texture and can easily weigh down your curls if used too much and will give no results if applied less. So to know the CORRECT pea size you need to do the try & error method cause it varies as per your hair porosity density & texture. 

I’ve medium to high porosity, medium density, dry hair. So I apply it twice the amount a low porosity fine hair curly would. 

This is my second bottle of cantu. I just love this product. It never fails to give amazing curls, condition being you have applied it in the correct quantity. 

Points to remember:
🪄EMULSIFY : take little cream, spray some water and rub your palms nicely to emulsify the product 
🪄 apply in rake in & then praying hand motion 
🪄 you can even do scrunching after applying the product 
🪄 do comb your hair for proper distribution
🪄 apply few drops of oil after the cream to lock the moisture 
🪄 apply the gel for extending curl definition for days.

Can’t believe it’s gonna be almost an year into rediscovering myself. 

Never did I thought that just changing the way my hair looks would bring so much confidence & self love. 

I’m so happy that I did trust the process and showed patience for the results to come. Though I still can’t say that my hair is totally healthy as what I experienced so far is that this is an on going process.

Things which I learned in the first year:
- first hair becomes healthy only then you can start seeing your curls forming nicely & that bounce.
- NO product can do the magic in just few washes (months)
- how much time the transformation takes depends on how damaged your hair is
- it’s NOT necessary to buy expensive products thinking that that’s why my hair isn’t getting that hold bounce shine. 
- it’s all about RIGHT product & RIGHT technique. Both are important.
- only YOU can understand whether your hair needs a protein or moisturising product 
- your CAN’T get curls like any other even if you use the same product & same technique 
- try & error is the ONLY way to know what is correct 

Thanks to so many of you for helping me learn from your content. For motivating & supporting me. Loads of love & blessings 💕

latestIgtvVideos.title: Age old hair oil recipe
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
An ancient ayurvedic treatment for hair loss, hair thinning & baldness- YELLOW BEE NEST OIL. 

All the ingredients are available on Amazon, even the bee hive. Updating the link of same in bio

Honeybees use a resin like substance to seal small crevices in their hive. This substance is know as Propolis. 

Propolis, or bee glue, is a substance used by bees to build their hives. Propolis contains many beneficial ingredients that can strengthen the immune system. New research shows that propolis may also be able to reduce or prevent hair loss. 

As per a study done in 2014, Japanese scientists believe the material could contain important clues for reversing hair loss & balding effect in humans.

The study, published in the Journal of Agricultural
and Food Chemistry, revealed that the team that
gave topical applications of propolis to mice that had been shaved or waxed, grew their fur back faster than those that weren't given the application, the propolis actually increased the number of cells engaged in hair growth. 

A second study, published in 2016 also found that propolis increased hair length and results in a greater percentage of hair follicles. 

These results indicate that propolis stimulates hair growth by inducing hair keratinocyte proliferation, the researchers concluded. This indicates that in some cases, propolis may help stimulate the growth of hair follicles that have stopped producing hair- causing hair to grow even in balding individuals.

Some individuals have an allergic reaction to the ingredients in propolis. Before applying oil, test for a reaction on a small area of the skin first.

Pls NOTE: this doesn’t work if you have Male pattern hair loss/baldness. Also further study is still being conducted on propolis as regards to hair growth. So it’s NOT scientifically proven but has shown promising results.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Apple cider vinegar for hair care
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
ACV rinse for shiny, frizz free, bouncy curls

♟What’s ACV ?
ACV = Apple cider vinegar 

♟Can we use any ACV?
Yes you can but ensure it is raw/unpasteurised aka ACV with “MOTHER”

♟Why ACV rinse?
1) It contains alpha-hydroxy acid which helps exfoliate scalp skin, and it's anti-inflammatory, which can help with dandruff too. 
2) For those dealing with hair issues such as itchy scalp or hair breakage, ACV rinse is a great remedy.
3) It contains good amounts of acetic acid. Hair that looks dull, brittle, or frizzy tends to be more alkaline or higher on the pH scale and an acid substance, like ACV, helps lower pH and brings hair health back into balance.
4) Apple cider vinegar’s antimicrobial powers are also well-supported by research. It could keep scalp problems related to fungus or bacteria at bay, thereby preventing itchy scalp. 

♟Why use AFTER conditioner?
As I have medium -high porosity hair so I use the ACV rinse AFTER conditioning so that it helps sealing the cuticles of my hair, nicely. I can also do this by doing final rinse with cold water but cause of all the benefits ACV gives, I prefer doing a ACV rinse once a month.

🎯How to use?
- to be done AFTER shampooing & conditioning hair.
- Mix 1 tablespoon of ACV in 250 ml of filtered water
- start dipping your hair length in the mix
- Also pour the ACV water mix on your scalp for exfoliation.
- Keep it atleast for 3-5 mins before finally rinse. 
- after cleaning it with plan water, style your hair as usual.

Pls note:
- the day when I do ACV rinse, I ensue to use a protein balanced deep conditioner and use a moisturising leave in after the rinse
- DONT over do it… as it can even dry you hair. Once in 20-25 days is ok.
- ALWAYS dilute ACV in water before using
- discontinue if you feel burning sensation
